WEBVTT

1
00:01:14.551 --> 00:01:17.145
<i>[man on television]
I can't hear you.</i>


2
00:01:17.187 --> 00:01:20.054
<i>It's them bells!</i>

3
00:01:20.090 --> 00:01:22.786
<i>I've had them in my ears
for ten hours.</i>


4
00:01:22.826 --> 00:01:26.353
<i>Ding, dong, ding, dong.</i>

5
00:01:27.797 --> 00:01:30.459
<i>[man 2] Hey, sergeant.
Where's Major Lance?</i>


6
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.469
<i>[man 3] We moved the CP back to
that stone building. The major's there.</i>


7
00:01:33.503 --> 00:01:35.266
<i>[man 2] Get him,
the colonel's here.</i>


8
00:01:36.873 --> 00:01:38.534
<i>Hold it!</i>

9
00:01:38.575 --> 00:01:40.475
<i>[guns firing in distance]</i>

10
00:01:48.785 --> 00:01:51.151
<i>[man] Colonel! 
Am I glad to see you!</i>

11
00:01:51.187 --> 00:01:55.385
<i>[man 2] Those bodies...
Get those bodies down!</i>


12
00:01:55.425 --> 00:01:59.122
<i>- What are you doing? Get 'em down!
- Of course. Yes, sir.</i>


13
00:01:59.162 --> 00:02:02.325
<i>- We've been under fire...
- I know you have, but I don't care!</i>


14
00:02:02.365 --> 00:02:07.064
<i>Get 'em down! Down!
Don't want those boys left up there.</i>


15
00:02:07.103 --> 00:02:11.164
<i>We're gonna hold this town till
the linkup does come, whenever it is.</i>


16
00:02:11.207 --> 00:02:16.201
<i>Today, tomorrow,
till hell freezes over.</i>


17
00:02:16.246 --> 00:02:18.373
<i>For their sake,
if for no other reason.</i>


18
00:02:18.415 --> 00:02:21.111
<i>- [man] Private?
- [man 2] Yes, sir.</i>


19
00:02:21.151 --> 00:02:24.279
<i>- [man] It's a hell of a war.
- [man 2] A privilege to serve with you.</i>


20
00:02:24.320 --> 00:02:28.950
<i>Well, God willing, we'll do
what we came here to do.</i>


21
00:02:28.992 --> 00:02:32.689
<i>- Ready, sir.
- Move out!</i>


22
00:02:35.065 --> 00:02:40.025
Pilgrim, we fought
for this country, too.


23
00:02:42.972 --> 00:02:44.735
Five postcard stamps, please.

24
00:02:46.309 --> 00:02:49.005
- Thank you. Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.


25
00:02:49.045 --> 00:02:51.536
Thank you so much.
Have a Merry Christmas.


26
00:02:53.216 --> 00:02:55.184
Airmail to Kingston, Jamaica.

27
00:03:00.256 --> 00:03:01.951
Stamps only?

28
00:03:03.226 --> 00:03:04.853
[speaks Jamaican]

29
00:03:07.864 --> 00:03:09.422
Twenty-cent stamp, please.

30
00:03:14.437 --> 00:03:17.736
Excuse me, sir?
Twenty-cent stamp, please.


31
00:03:28.351 --> 00:03:29.943
- Rodolfo.
- You.


32
00:03:29.986 --> 00:03:31.977
[gun fires]

33
00:03:32.021 --> 00:03:34.251
[screaming]

34
00:04:11.327 --> 00:04:13.295
- Hey, buddy.
- Um, press.


35
00:04:13.329 --> 00:04:14.921
OK.

36
00:04:21.704 --> 00:04:24.696
- Are you Detective Ricci?
- That's my story.


37
00:04:24.741 --> 00:04:25.969
I heard about you.

38
00:04:26.009 --> 00:04:28.876
[grunts] Yeah, well,
you oughta change friends then.


39
00:04:28.912 --> 00:04:31.813
<i>I'm Tim Boyle. 
Daily News.</i>

40
00:04:31.848 --> 00:04:34.783
<i>- What happened?
- Read about it in the New York Post.</i>


41
00:04:34.817 --> 00:04:38.719
<i>They left here two hours ago along with
The Times, Newsday and every channel</i>


42
00:04:38.755 --> 00:04:42.714
you can get on TV with a wire hanger.
Ain't you ever heard of the early bird?


43
00:04:42.759 --> 00:04:45.626
- Christ.
- Go find a wailing wall.


44
00:04:45.662 --> 00:04:47.596
- I got lost.
- Comin' here?


45
00:04:47.630 --> 00:04:49.689
Find another way
for a dollar to change pockets.


46
00:04:49.732 --> 00:04:53.133
- It's my first day as a reporter.
- It's probably your last.


47
00:04:53.169 --> 00:04:55.831
Welcome to New York.
Be like Governor Rockefeller:


48
00:04:55.872 --> 00:04:58.568
- Come and go at the same time.
- Give me some angle.


49
00:04:58.608 --> 00:05:01.668
All I can give you
is an empty feeling, kid.


50
00:05:01.711 --> 00:05:04.839
The perp's over at Bellevue,
eighth floor peanut gallery.


51
00:05:04.881 --> 00:05:07.315
The victim's deader
than yesterday's beer.


52
00:05:07.350 --> 00:05:09.944
Heard he wasn't special
when he was breathing.


53
00:05:09.986 --> 00:05:13.444
My next job's gonna be stuffin'
ballot boxes on Staten Island.


54
00:05:13.489 --> 00:05:18.085
Remind me to vote. I live there.
Most cops do. Go home, kid.


55
00:05:18.127 --> 00:05:19.992
- Don't stop for bread.
- Come on.


56
00:05:20.029 --> 00:05:23.465
Gotta be something I can work.
Can I give you a tip on a hot horse?


57
00:05:23.499 --> 00:05:26.263
I'll play Santa at the PA
on Christmas Day. Or I'll...


58
00:05:26.302 --> 00:05:30.295
I'll pay Hong Kong Sue over on Forty
Deuce to blow your noodle like Satchmo.


59
00:05:30.340 --> 00:05:32.467
How about I put a story
in your hip pocket?


60
00:05:32.508 --> 00:05:34.601
"Good Cop Helps Poor Kids."

61
00:05:34.644 --> 00:05:38.375
Honest to Jesus, you get three months
of Saturdays out of it. Come on.


62
00:05:38.414 --> 00:05:40.882
I can't go back to scratching out obits.

63
00:05:42.919 --> 00:05:44.944
See those guys?
Don't turn around.


64
00:05:44.988 --> 00:05:49.084
They're rolling up to Harlem
to sniff around the perp's apartment.


65
00:05:49.125 --> 00:05:53.061
Only case that dynamic duo has cracked
has Schaefer written on the side,


66
00:05:53.096 --> 00:05:56.759
but maybe you'll see something.
Don't quote those gumflappers.


67
00:05:56.799 --> 00:05:58.630
- You need a quote, you call me.
- OK.


68
00:05:58.668 --> 00:06:01.159
- Haggerty, Dillard!
- Yeah, what's up?


69
00:06:01.204 --> 00:06:05.231
- Take this guy uptown with you.
- Thank you. Thank you.


70
00:06:05.275 --> 00:06:07.800
- Come on.
- All right.


71
00:06:19.088 --> 00:06:22.148
We'll start in the living room
and work our way back.


72
00:06:24.327 --> 00:06:26.420
Close the door behind you, kid.

73
00:06:49.018 --> 00:06:51.350
This perp is very, very religious.

74
00:06:51.387 --> 00:06:54.823
Nothing wrong with being
in good standing with the Lord.


75
00:06:59.762 --> 00:07:02.287
And a war hero, too.
Look at this, a Purple Heart.


76
00:07:02.332 --> 00:07:05.392
Hey, Keith, the Brown Bomber.

77
00:07:05.435 --> 00:07:09.269
[Keith] Muhammad Ali would've knocked
him out. Way too fast for Joe Louis.


78
00:07:09.305 --> 00:07:11.205
He can run, but he can't hide.

79
00:07:22.485 --> 00:07:25.113
Hey, Dan, what the hell is this?

80
00:07:25.154 --> 00:07:28.715
- [Dan] What you got there?
- I don't know. It's heavy.


81
00:07:28.758 --> 00:07:32.717
Whatever this is, it ain't junior-grade.
This thing looks expensive.


82
00:07:32.762 --> 00:07:38.530
My wife claws around flea markets
looking for this crap every weekend.


83
00:07:38.568 --> 00:07:40.433
I'm telling you, this ain't normal.

84
00:07:40.470 --> 00:07:42.165
This definitely ain't normal.

85
00:07:42.205 --> 00:07:45.072
- Back up, buddy.
- Sorry.


86
00:07:45.108 --> 00:07:46.632
[Keith] No problem.

87
00:07:46.676 --> 00:07:49.474
- Professor Brooks?
- Yes.


88
00:07:51.647 --> 00:07:56.482
I get a lot of these things.
Old rocks. Antique specials.


89
00:07:56.519 --> 00:07:59.420
It seems like every
schmuck in the world


90
00:07:59.455 --> 00:08:03.482
who finds a backyard arrowhead
mistakes me for Iris.


91
00:08:03.526 --> 00:08:04.959
Put it here.

92
00:08:04.994 --> 00:08:09.658
From Greek mythology.
She is the faithful voice of Zeus.


93
00:08:09.699 --> 00:08:14.363
She flies from place to place
and commands respect


94
00:08:14.404 --> 00:08:17.805
from mortals and from im...

95
00:08:19.709 --> 00:08:21.336
...immortals.

96
00:08:23.746 --> 00:08:26.874
- Where the hell'd you get this?
- From a perp's apartment.


97
00:08:26.916 --> 00:08:29.180
- It's got this mark...
- Don't touch it.


98
00:08:29.218 --> 00:08:34.918
This is over 450 years old.

99
00:08:34.957 --> 00:08:38.757
It's the missing Primavera
from the Santa Trinita.


100
00:08:38.795 --> 00:08:41.263
<i>Is that the Niña, the Pinta
or the Santa Maria?</i>


101
00:08:41.297 --> 00:08:43.356
Oh, for God sakes, detective.

102
00:08:43.399 --> 00:08:46.391
It's the oldest elliptic

103
00:08:46.436 --> 00:08:49.803
arch bridge in the world.

104
00:08:49.839 --> 00:08:53.366
It's in Florence, Italy.

105
00:08:53.409 --> 00:08:55.673
Built by Ammanati.

106
00:08:55.711 --> 00:08:59.112
This was one of four statues on it.

107
00:08:59.148 --> 00:09:03.983
The Primavera, meaning "spring."

108
00:09:04.020 --> 00:09:05.851
This head has been missing

109
00:09:05.888 --> 00:09:10.518
since the Nazis blew up
the bridge in 1944.


110
00:09:10.560 --> 00:09:15.793
My God! This is a gold mine!

111
00:09:16.599 --> 00:09:18.590
A gold mine!

112
00:09:23.206 --> 00:09:24.730
Yo!

113
00:09:30.546 --> 00:09:32.411
[elevator dings]

114
00:09:43.626 --> 00:09:47.392
Merry Christmas. 
From Tim Boyle.

115
00:09:47.430 --> 00:09:49.523
Oh, wise guy.

116
00:10:18.327 --> 00:10:20.522
[Tim] Mr. Hector Negron?

117
00:10:32.808 --> 00:10:34.901
[children shouting]

118
00:10:54.964 --> 00:10:57.364
[in Italian]
Darling, come back to bed.


119
00:10:57.400 --> 00:10:58.890
Please. Enough.

120
00:10:58.935 --> 00:11:01.597
I need a little break, OK, baby?

121
00:11:07.109 --> 00:11:10.010
[Tim] They say you haven't
spoken or eaten in two days.


122
00:11:10.046 --> 00:11:13.072
They'll try to force-feed you.

123
00:11:13.115 --> 00:11:15.413
Make you rise, like Jesus.

124
00:11:21.891 --> 00:11:24.860
Come on. I've hiked all over
New York asking about you.


125
00:11:24.894 --> 00:11:27.692
I talked to everybody.
Cops, your sister.


126
00:11:27.730 --> 00:11:31.291
Spoke to your cousin in San Juan.
You're clean as a board of health.


127
00:11:31.334 --> 00:11:33.996
You got no kids, no debts, no enemies.

128
00:11:34.036 --> 00:11:36.163
Four years in the service. Purple Heart.

129
00:11:36.205 --> 00:11:38.571
Twenty-five years
of a great marriage,


130
00:11:38.608 --> 00:11:41.873
till your wife's heart gave out.

131
00:11:43.479 --> 00:11:47.472
So why you stick a German Luger
in a guy's chest


132
00:11:47.516 --> 00:11:51.850
three months short of your retirement?
Five million dollars.


133
00:11:51.887 --> 00:11:54.856
That's how much that head would
draw on the black market.


134
00:11:54.890 --> 00:11:58.587
What's it doin' buried there
on the bottom of your closet?


135
00:12:06.435 --> 00:12:08.835
You're looking at 25 to life, pal.

136
00:12:08.871 --> 00:12:12.363
Unless you can afford a lawyer,
you're gonna swallow happy pills


137
00:12:12.408 --> 00:12:15.206
in this nuthouse the rest of your life.

138
00:12:15.244 --> 00:12:20.011
But my story could help you.
And you need help, mac.


139
00:12:24.420 --> 00:12:29.016
[woman, in Italian] Enrico, what kind
of art dealer specializes in Nazi art?


140
00:12:29.058 --> 00:12:31.891
Because it's a lucrative business.

141
00:12:34.130 --> 00:12:37.099
[in Italian] You Americans love work
more than you love 'love.'


142
00:12:37.133 --> 00:12:38.293
[groans]

143
00:12:39.769 --> 00:12:42.704
[in Italian] My love,
are you ignoring me?


144
00:12:44.507 --> 00:12:46.304
[Keith] Pina, no.
Don't come over here.


145
00:12:49.578 --> 00:12:52.012
[in Italian] Enrico, you said
you only needed ten minutes.


146
00:12:52.048 --> 00:12:54.915
I gotta catch up. World might've
ended, I wouldn't know


147
00:12:54.950 --> 00:12:58.147
'cause we've been going at it
two days. For crying out loud.


148
00:12:58.187 --> 00:13:00.155
[in Italian] The world is still here.

149
00:13:00.189 --> 00:13:01.520
You and I are still here.

150
00:13:01.557 --> 00:13:03.252
Baby, not right now.

151
00:13:04.360 --> 00:13:06.885
There you go. Excuse me.

152
00:13:08.064 --> 00:13:09.531
OK?

153
00:13:11.834 --> 00:13:14.564
Oh, God. Oh, that feels good.

154
00:13:15.538 --> 00:13:17.403
[Pina giggling]

155
00:13:19.608 --> 00:13:21.075
You're killing me, baby.

156
00:13:21.110 --> 00:13:23.271
[in Italian] Yes, 
I love you to death.

157
00:13:56.212 --> 00:13:57.941
[sighs]

158
00:14:15.464 --> 00:14:17.364
I...

159
00:14:18.801 --> 00:14:21.793
Hmm? What is it, Mr. Negron?

160
00:14:24.607 --> 00:14:26.040
I... I know.

161
00:14:27.676 --> 00:14:28.802
You know what?

162
00:14:34.750 --> 00:14:37.310
I know who the sleeping man is!

163
00:14:37.353 --> 00:14:41.756
- [Tim] You know what?
- I know who the sleeping man is.


164
00:14:41.791 --> 00:14:45.386
[bells tolling]

165
00:14:45.427 --> 00:14:48.828
[child yelling in Italian]

166
00:15:47.823 --> 00:15:51.850
[man whimpering]
Mama. I want mama.


167
00:16:15.184 --> 00:16:18.620
Kill me now! Kill me now,
I wanna go home to my mama!


168
00:16:18.654 --> 00:16:22.021
I don't wanna be here.
I wanna go home!


169
00:16:22.057 --> 00:16:25.288
Kill me now! Kill me now!

170
00:16:25.327 --> 00:16:29.457
Oh, Jesus, I want my mama!
I don't wanna die! I don't wanna die!


171
00:16:29.498 --> 00:16:30.590
Shh!

172
00:16:30.633 --> 00:16:34.296
- Hector, shut him the fuck up.
- Yes, sir.


173
00:16:34.336 --> 00:16:37.328
- I don't wanna die!
- Shut the fuck up!


174
00:16:37.373 --> 00:16:42.140
[whispering] You wanna get us all
killed? That's your mama right now.


175
00:16:42.177 --> 00:16:45.271
- This far enough?
- Keep movin'.


176
00:16:45.314 --> 00:16:50.547
- You doin' fine, big fella.
- Help me, Lord. Help me, Lord.


177
00:16:50.586 --> 00:16:53.384
Help me, Lord,
I'm prepared for Thee.


178
00:16:53.422 --> 00:16:56.789
- Get off of me, sniper bait!
- Bishop, Train, switch flanks.


179
00:16:56.825 --> 00:16:59.157
Bishop, take outer.
Train, take the inner.


180
00:16:59.194 --> 00:17:00.991
- What's that?
- Take inner flank.


181
00:17:01.030 --> 00:17:03.590
- What's that?
- Come on. Switch places, dummy.


182
00:17:03.632 --> 00:17:05.122
Gimme some room.

183
00:17:09.071 --> 00:17:12.234
Hey, Bishop.
Why we got to cross this river?


184
00:17:12.274 --> 00:17:14.538
They sellin' hoecakes
and beer on the other side.


185
00:17:14.576 --> 00:17:15.668
[laughs]

186
00:17:18.714 --> 00:17:22.172
- My good luck charm gives me strength.
- Piece of shit you found


187
00:17:22.217 --> 00:17:24.378
in the gutter in Florence?

188
00:17:24.420 --> 00:17:27.412
Couldn't draw a bowl of turtle soup
from Uncle Amos with that.


189
00:17:27.456 --> 00:17:28.821
Worth more than a bowl of soup!

190
00:17:28.857 --> 00:17:30.757
Shh!

191
00:17:30.793 --> 00:17:32.761
Train.

192
00:17:32.795 --> 00:17:36.663
Hector, you speak Italian.
Cut-off head worth somethin'?


193
00:17:36.699 --> 00:17:39.634
<i>- Yo speaky Puerto Rican, man.
- Hey, muzzle that.</i>


194
00:17:39.668 --> 00:17:41.135
Keep moving.

195
00:18:51.640 --> 00:18:53.073
[man speaks German]

196
00:18:53.108 --> 00:18:56.805
<i>[man on radio] Germany calling,
Germany calling.</i>


197
00:18:56.845 --> 00:18:59.678
<i>Guten morgen, 92nd Division.</i>

198
00:18:59.715 --> 00:19:03.617
Buffalo soldiers, welcome to the war.

199
00:19:03.652 --> 00:19:07.418
<i>[woman on loudspeaker]
We've been waiting for you.</i>


200
00:19:07.456 --> 00:19:11.586
<i>Do you know our German Wehrmacht
has been here digging bunkers</i>


201
00:19:11.627 --> 00:19:15.529
<i>for six months on the Gothic Line?
Waiting.</i>


202
00:19:15.564 --> 00:19:20.501
<i>Your white commanders
won't tell you that, of course.</i>


203
00:19:20.536 --> 00:19:25.530
<i>Why? Because they
don't care if you die.</i>


204
00:19:25.574 --> 00:19:26.632
[whimpering]

205
00:19:26.675 --> 00:19:30.202
<i>But the German people have
nothing against the Negro.</i>


206
00:19:30.245 --> 00:19:34.181
That's why I'm warning you now,
with all my heart and soul.


207
00:19:34.216 --> 00:19:36.878
Save yourself, 
Negro brothers.

208
00:19:36.919 --> 00:19:40.218
<i>Why die for a nation
that doesn't want you?</i>


209
00:19:40.255 --> 00:19:44.555
<i>A nation that treats you like a slave.</i>

210
00:19:44.593 --> 00:19:46.060
<i>Did I say slave?</i>

211
00:19:46.095 --> 00:19:48.893
Yes, I did.

212
00:19:48.931 --> 00:19:52.196
[speaking German]
Why don't they shut her up?


213
00:19:52.234 --> 00:19:54.065
What is she saying?

214
00:19:54.103 --> 00:19:57.129
Berlin can afford to pipe
that garbage all the way here


215
00:19:57.172 --> 00:19:59.231
but can't give us potato soup.

216
00:20:01.777 --> 00:20:04.337
Individual guns only, on my command.

217
00:20:06.081 --> 00:20:09.539
We have enough ammo
for an hour, maybe two.


218
00:20:09.585 --> 00:20:11.780
<i>[woman] Look around you.</i>

219
00:20:11.820 --> 00:20:15.756
<i>Do you see any white soldiers
in the river next to you?</i>


220
00:20:15.791 --> 00:20:20.387
<i>Are they sending any white
soldiers to die with you today?</i>


221
00:20:20.429 --> 00:20:23.489
<i>- Of course not!
- [man] Steady, ya'll. Adolf Hitler.</i>


222
00:20:23.532 --> 00:20:26.524
Spreadin' that nonsense.
Don't believe a word of that!


223
00:20:26.568 --> 00:20:30.163
Lyin' bastard thinks we monkeys,
apes, baboons, subhuman.


224
00:20:31.273 --> 00:20:32.535
Show him who we are.

225
00:20:32.574 --> 00:20:34.508
[woman] Think of your poor children,

226
00:20:34.543 --> 00:20:38.343
your families suffering at home.

227
00:20:38.380 --> 00:20:41.281
<i>The American white man</i>

228
00:20:41.316 --> 00:20:44.774
<i>is raping your wives and daughters.</i>

229
00:20:44.820 --> 00:20:48.312
<i>Jody is busy right now in your
bedroom, with your wife,</i>


230
00:20:48.357 --> 00:20:52.987
<i>your daughters, even your sons.
And who will stop him if you die today?</i>


231
00:20:53.028 --> 00:20:56.122
<i>Do you think the profitmongers
in Washington, D.C.</i>


232
00:20:56.165 --> 00:21:01.694
<i>care about your children?
They're not thinking of your children!</i>


233
00:21:01.737 --> 00:21:03.762
<i>They're home right now.</i>

234
00:21:03.805 --> 00:21:08.970
Asleep, in a nice warm bed.

235
00:21:10.579 --> 00:21:13.047
<i>Think about the sacrifice
you're making,</i>


236
00:21:13.081 --> 00:21:17.177
<i>just for the privilege of being
second-class citizens back home.</i>


237
00:21:17.219 --> 00:21:19.881
<i>Where can you vote?</i>

238
00:21:19.922 --> 00:21:23.358
<i>Come to the winning side</i>

239
00:21:23.392 --> 00:21:26.953
<i>and, please, teach me those dances.</i>

240
00:21:26.995 --> 00:21:30.624
<i>That Lindy Hop and the Black Bottom.</i>

241
00:21:30.666 --> 00:21:33.191
<i>War is folly, boys.</i>

242
00:21:33.235 --> 00:21:37.171
Better to drop your guns,
give up and dance!


243
00:21:37.206 --> 00:21:41.836
<i>Come out of that cold water, cats!</i>

244
00:21:42.511 --> 00:21:44.741
[speaking German]
You got any more biscuits?


245
00:21:44.780 --> 00:21:45.804
No.

246
00:21:45.847 --> 00:21:47.405
- Or anything else?
- Not for you.


247
00:21:47.449 --> 00:21:49.576
I'll give you money
for a vitamin biscuit.


248
00:21:49.618 --> 00:21:51.279
Go over and beg the Blacks.

249
00:21:53.355 --> 00:21:56.256
What about you?
You a replacement?


250
00:21:57.226 --> 00:21:58.989
65th Army Corps.

251
00:21:59.027 --> 00:22:01.757
I thought they were freezing
their asses off in Russia.


252
00:22:01.797 --> 00:22:03.355
- So?
- You got any biscuits?


253
00:22:03.398 --> 00:22:04.592
No.

254
00:22:04.633 --> 00:22:06.931
They must have given you something.

255
00:22:06.969 --> 00:22:08.630
If I die, you
can have all my rations,

256
00:22:08.670 --> 00:22:10.467
but for now,
SHUT THE FUCK UP!!!


257
00:22:10.505 --> 00:22:12.939
I got a hole in my stomach.

258
00:22:12.975 --> 00:22:17.275
<i>[woman] Come on over.
Feel the warmth of the German people.</i>


259
00:22:17.312 --> 00:22:21.009
[speaking German] I can't hear a thing
over that damn whore's prattling.


260
00:22:21.049 --> 00:22:25.110
<i>[woman] We have hot food,
fried chicken,</i>


261
00:22:25.153 --> 00:22:29.453
<i>greens, candied yams
and even delicious biscuits</i>


262
00:22:29.491 --> 00:22:32.824
<i>straight from the oven,
just like your mama cooks.</i>


263
00:22:32.861 --> 00:22:35.489
Hey, boys.

264
00:22:35.530 --> 00:22:40.661
I have two big white biscuits
right here for you.


265
00:22:40.702 --> 00:22:46.607
<i>Buffalo soldiers. 
Hey, cool cats.</i>

266
00:22:46.642 --> 00:22:49.611
<i>Do I have something
special for you.</i>


267
00:22:49.645 --> 00:22:53.046
<i>And you can have all you want.</i>

268
00:22:53.081 --> 00:22:57.017
That goddamned bitch
is gonna start a race riot.


269
00:22:57.052 --> 00:23:00.317
Is that a white woman, officer?
What's your name, soldier?


270
00:23:00.355 --> 00:23:03.347
- Lieutenant Birdsong, sir.
- Who is that?


271
00:23:03.392 --> 00:23:05.383
- You heard of Tokyo Rose, sir?
- Yeah.


272
00:23:05.427 --> 00:23:09.659
This is the Kraut version. Axis Sally.
She visits us from time to time.


273
00:23:09.698 --> 00:23:11.757
- Is she American?
- Don't know, sir.


274
00:23:11.800 --> 00:23:15.429
<i>[Axis Sally] Have you ever wondered
how it felt to be free?</i>


275
00:23:15.470 --> 00:23:21.033
<i>To be your own man?
To stand tall?</i>


276
00:23:21.076 --> 00:23:24.637
Need a sniper to splat that nag's
brains all over the Serchio.


277
00:23:24.680 --> 00:23:28.138
I can't see a thing outta these.
Roust me up a better set of cans.


278
00:23:28.183 --> 00:23:30.674
Right now, and a drink of water,
on the double.


279
00:23:30.719 --> 00:23:32.311
Yes, sir.

280
00:23:32.354 --> 00:23:35.687
[man] Negative, Abel Six. Stay firm
and await further commands. Over.


281
00:23:35.724 --> 00:23:38.249
What's he gonna do,
give her a smack on the lips?


282
00:23:38.293 --> 00:23:42.457
He sets himself up a mile away with fire
control, then complains he can't see.


283
00:23:42.497 --> 00:23:44.897
Oughta be with his men
like a real captain.


284
00:23:44.933 --> 00:23:47.026
He ain't been here
long enough to learn.


285
00:23:47.069 --> 00:23:50.527
Yeah, and you won't be here
long neither, listenin' to him.


286
00:23:50.572 --> 00:23:52.164
[speaks German]
Stupid white man.


287
00:23:53.909 --> 00:23:57.606
Right now!
Let's go, goddamn it.


288
00:24:00.349 --> 00:24:03.147
New cans, fresh H2O, sir.

289
00:24:03.185 --> 00:24:06.313
<i>[Axis Sally] Buffalo soldiers,</i>

290
00:24:06.355 --> 00:24:09.518
<i>take the first step, fellas.</i>

291
00:24:09.558 --> 00:24:12.459
<i>We have warm fires. Pretty...</i>

292
00:24:12.494 --> 00:24:15.224
- Hold that.
- Yes, sir.


293
00:24:15.263 --> 00:24:18.460
Next time I want you
to take the caps off.


294
00:24:18.500 --> 00:24:19.592
Yes, sir.

295
00:24:19.634 --> 00:24:23.968
<i>German Frauleins like big strong bucks</i>

296
00:24:24.005 --> 00:24:26.405
more than lollipops.

297
00:24:26.441 --> 00:24:29.069
<i>And we love lollipops.</i>

298
00:24:29.111 --> 00:24:31.170
She the one selling
hoecakes and beer?


299
00:24:31.213 --> 00:24:33.204
Your brain's had a rough shuffle.

300
00:24:33.248 --> 00:24:36.081
For the last time, muzzle that shit!

301
00:24:36.118 --> 00:24:37.813
- [machine gun fire]
- Coming down!


302
00:24:37.853 --> 00:24:40.321
- Let's go!
- Suppressing fire!


303
00:24:42.090 --> 00:24:43.648
[screaming]

304
00:24:48.130 --> 00:24:49.995
[yelling]

305
00:24:56.304 --> 00:24:57.896
Withdraw! Withdraw!

306
00:25:14.022 --> 00:25:16.286
[man] Withdraw! Withdraw!

307
00:25:19.628 --> 00:25:21.118
[grunts]

308
00:25:31.940 --> 00:25:35.706
Come on, Train! Come on, move!
Go, go, go, go, go!


309
00:25:39.548 --> 00:25:41.413
[man screaming]

310
00:25:51.359 --> 00:25:52.485
Fire!

311
00:25:54.596 --> 00:25:56.359
Fire!

312
00:26:02.337 --> 00:26:06.865
George Company. Request artillery
to grids four, seven, nine and 1-6!


313
00:26:06.908 --> 00:26:09.342
<i>- Send the mail!
- Where the hell are you?</i>


314
00:26:09.377 --> 00:26:10.867
- We've crossed!
- You what?


315
00:26:10.912 --> 00:26:12.607
We're with Uncle Jerry!

316
00:26:12.647 --> 00:26:16.105
Put smoke, H.A. to grids four,
seven, nine and 1-6!


317
00:26:16.151 --> 00:26:19.177
It's impossible to be
on the other side of that river.


318
00:26:19.221 --> 00:26:23.317
- Is that Huggs calling out a grid?
- Huggs! What is your position?


319
00:26:23.358 --> 00:26:27.226
Sir! Huggs is down!
Stamps here! Send the mail!


320
00:26:27.262 --> 00:26:31.028
- Send the mail now!
- Write this name down. Stamps.


321
00:26:31.066 --> 00:26:32.829
Stamps. He's across?

322
00:26:36.371 --> 00:26:38.271
He's lying.

323
00:26:38.306 --> 00:26:41.571
Now, set fire to grids two-three,
two-four and two-five.


324
00:26:41.610 --> 00:26:45.478
- That's Rudden, Fox Company.
- George Company? They've crossed?


325
00:26:45.514 --> 00:26:48.210
I'm new to this outfit
doesn't mean I gotta argue


326
00:26:48.250 --> 00:26:53.051
with goddamn second lieutenants acting
like uppity Negroes. You follow me?


327
00:26:54.489 --> 00:26:56.218
Do you follow me, soldier?

328
00:26:56.258 --> 00:26:59.591
Yes, sir.

329
00:26:59.628 --> 00:27:02.722
Smoke and fire to grids
two-three, two-four, two-five.


330
00:27:02.764 --> 00:27:05.028
- Sir.
- Smoke and fire to grids two-three,


331
00:27:05.066 --> 00:27:08.433
- two-four, two five. Over!
- Smoke and fire to grids two-three,


332
00:27:08.470 --> 00:27:10.700
- two-four and two-five!
- [grunts]


333
00:27:10.739 --> 00:27:13.207
Adolf Hitler, this is for you.

334
00:27:15.210 --> 00:27:17.041
What the hell!

335
00:27:19.714 --> 00:27:21.238
Radio!

336
00:27:21.283 --> 00:27:23.274
- Withdraw!
- Withdrawing!


337
00:27:23.318 --> 00:27:26.549
[Stamps] Cease fire! Cease...

338
00:27:26.588 --> 00:27:28.954
Adjust fire! Adjust fire!

339
00:27:28.990 --> 00:27:30.651
I repeat, adjust fire!

340
00:27:30.692 --> 00:27:35.493
Request artillery to grids four,
seven, nine and 1-6! Send the mail!


341
00:27:35.530 --> 00:27:37.020
[speaks German]

342
00:27:37.065 --> 00:27:38.327
Fire!

343
00:27:39.167 --> 00:27:40.464
[screaming]

344
00:27:42.571 --> 00:27:44.163
Fire!

345
00:27:50.979 --> 00:27:52.640
Incoming!

346
00:28:00.388 --> 00:28:01.548
[screams]

347
00:28:09.731 --> 00:28:11.528
[screaming]

348
00:28:11.566 --> 00:28:13.295
Get off me!

349
00:28:13.335 --> 00:28:14.825
Help!

350
00:28:16.605 --> 00:28:19.631
Help! Help!

351
00:28:39.527 --> 00:28:41.051
Cover me!

352
00:28:55.543 --> 00:28:57.101
[screaming]

353
00:29:46.528 --> 00:29:49.895
[both panting]

354
00:30:00.041 --> 00:30:02.009
[distant artillery firing]

355
00:30:43.852 --> 00:30:46.446
Come on. Come on.

356
00:30:59.400 --> 00:31:03.461
OK. You and me gotta
get to that tree. OK?


357
00:31:03.505 --> 00:31:05.370
- All right.
- Go!


358
00:31:08.376 --> 00:31:10.901
Go, go, go, go, go, go, go!

359
00:31:14.282 --> 00:31:16.614
Get down, get down, get down!

360
00:31:20.155 --> 00:31:21.850
[artillery whistling]

361
00:31:22.857 --> 00:31:24.688
[grunting]

362
00:31:26.795 --> 00:31:28.888
[yelling] Oh! Oh, Lord!

363
00:31:28.930 --> 00:31:32.696
Oh, I'm coming up yonder!
Meet me, Jesus!


364
00:31:32.734 --> 00:31:34.929
- Shut up.
- Oh, Bishop, they got you, too.


365
00:31:34.969 --> 00:31:38.166
- No. Listen!
- Is we dead, Bishop? We dead?


366
00:31:38.206 --> 00:31:41.141
No, listen to me. You was dead.
OK? But I brung ya back.


367
00:31:41.176 --> 00:31:45.044
You ain't dyin' till I get my
money. You owe me $1,400.


368
00:31:48.817 --> 00:31:52.981
Look here. Go check out that
haystack. That shit is moving.


369
00:31:54.122 --> 00:31:55.646
What in the world?

370
00:32:02.096 --> 00:32:03.256
[in Italian] Arturo!

371
00:32:04.299 --> 00:32:06.290
Arturo, where are you?

372
00:32:08.336 --> 00:32:10.270
Arturo!

373
00:32:12.540 --> 00:32:13.939
Arturo.

374
00:32:31.893 --> 00:32:34.020
[in Italian] Beautiful.

375
00:32:34.062 --> 00:32:35.689
Where did you find it?

376
00:32:42.337 --> 00:32:43.998
Watch me throw it.

377
00:32:47.008 --> 00:32:48.999
<i>[singing] # Little black face</i>

378
00:32:49.043 --> 00:32:50.874
<i># Beautiful Abyssinian</i>

379
00:32:50.912 --> 00:32:54.507
<i># Wait and hope,
The hour is already near</i>


380
00:32:54.549 --> 00:32:56.278
<i># When we will be</i>

381
00:32:56.317 --> 00:32:58.217
<i># Close to you</i>

382
00:32:58.253 --> 00:33:01.416
<i># And there to give you
a different law and a different King #</i>


383
00:33:06.728 --> 00:33:10.095
Arturo! Now, I am nine years old.

384
00:33:21.943 --> 00:33:23.672
Move, sniper bait, go!

385
00:33:36.791 --> 00:33:41.660
[boy speaking Italian] Okay,
maybe I'm eight. I'm really only eight.


386
00:33:41.696 --> 00:33:43.220
[boy groaning]

387
00:34:02.450 --> 00:34:05.078
Good God!

388
00:34:05.119 --> 00:34:08.282
[in Italian] A Chocolate Giant.

389
00:34:11.492 --> 00:34:13.619
- [grunting]
- [in Italian] Help me.


390
00:34:13.661 --> 00:34:16.630
I'll give you a banana,
Chocolate Giant.


391
00:34:16.664 --> 00:34:18.564
[both grunting]

392
00:34:20.601 --> 00:34:24.469
Sorry, boy. I done gived it
every muscle I got.


393
00:34:24.505 --> 00:34:27.372
[in Italian] Use your tail,
Chocolate Giant.


394
00:34:32.780 --> 00:34:35.408
Jesus is waitin' on you, child.

395
00:34:36.718 --> 00:34:39.812
This world ain't worth
a pinch of snuff nohow.


396
00:34:41.456 --> 00:34:43.947
[in Italian] No, please don't leave.

397
00:34:43.992 --> 00:34:46.688
Oh, my God, it hurts.

398
00:34:52.000 --> 00:34:54.662
Come on. Come on.

399
00:35:01.709 --> 00:35:03.643
[straining]

400
00:35:07.115 --> 00:35:09.106
[straining, yelling]

401
00:35:14.522 --> 00:35:16.786
[gasping]

402
00:35:20.161 --> 00:35:22.925
Boy! Hey, boy! Hey!

403
00:35:22.964 --> 00:35:25.228
Boy. You breathin'?

404
00:35:26.701 --> 00:35:29.898
[in Italian] Giant,
you don't taste like chocolate.


405
00:35:52.960 --> 00:35:54.359
[in German]
Don't shoot. Don't shoot.


406
00:35:55.563 --> 00:35:56.962
You can't kill me.

407
00:35:57.932 --> 00:35:59.160
I'm invisible!

408
00:36:40.842 --> 00:36:44.209
Come on, boy. Come on.

409
00:36:44.245 --> 00:36:45.371
Let's go.

410
00:36:46.180 --> 00:36:48.205
[artillery shrieking]

411
00:36:54.388 --> 00:36:57.152
[Bishop] Train! Train!

412
00:36:57.191 --> 00:36:59.056
[whispering] Oh, no.

413
00:37:23.017 --> 00:37:25.884
Where's Train?

414
00:37:25.920 --> 00:37:28.286
He ain't...
He ain't make it.


415
00:37:28.322 --> 00:37:31.553
That nigger's dumber than a dime.
You sent him over the hill?


416
00:37:31.592 --> 00:37:34.390
- I ain't tell him to risk his life.
- It's nobody's fault.


417
00:37:34.428 --> 00:37:36.453
That boy was born over the hill.

418
00:37:39.233 --> 00:37:40.928
[Bishop] Follow me.

419
00:37:58.386 --> 00:38:01.184
<i>- [man grunts]
- Special delivery for the Führer.</i>


420
00:38:23.611 --> 00:38:25.670
[in Italian] Holy Mother of God.

421
00:39:05.419 --> 00:39:06.909
Train!

422
00:39:09.590 --> 00:39:11.251
Train!

423
00:39:11.292 --> 00:39:14.318
Train, you damn fool!
I thought you was dead!


424
00:39:16.697 --> 00:39:18.722
[Hector] Told you
he was going over the hill.


425
00:39:25.873 --> 00:39:29.206
[whispering] Oh, no.
The fuck is he...


426
00:39:29.243 --> 00:39:31.711
We wait here till dark,
and then we cross back.


427
00:39:31.746 --> 00:39:33.111
Good.

428
00:39:33.147 --> 00:39:35.445
[speaks Spanish]
This shit is heavy as hell.


429
00:39:41.088 --> 00:39:43.249
Bishop!

430
00:39:43.291 --> 00:39:46.590
- Where you going?
- Y'all go on back across that river.


431
00:39:46.627 --> 00:39:49.596
The only person with any luck
around here is him.


432
00:39:49.630 --> 00:39:52.895
Plus, he owe me $1,400.
That's the kind of money


433
00:39:52.933 --> 00:39:55.265
that can set me up
for the rest of my life.


434
00:39:55.303 --> 00:39:57.294
Even if the rest
of my life is today.

435
00:40:10.584 --> 00:40:12.745
[grunts, in Spanish]
To hell with this.


436
00:40:15.189 --> 00:40:16.588
I'm up shit's creek.

437
00:40:56.831 --> 00:41:00.096
- Jesse Owens!
- [Train] Jack Johnson.


438
00:41:00.134 --> 00:41:03.126
You go talk to your wife up there.

439
00:41:22.656 --> 00:41:27.059
I never felt so lonesome
in my whole life, Bishop.


440
00:41:27.094 --> 00:41:30.928
- I been dreaming a lot.
- Yeah.


441
00:41:30.965 --> 00:41:35.868
Nigga, I ain't really interested in your
dreams. I want my motherfucking money.


442
00:41:35.903 --> 00:41:39.134
I got something's
worth more than $1,400.


443
00:41:40.941 --> 00:41:43.705
Better than black cat's bones.
Make you invisible.


444
00:41:43.744 --> 00:41:45.575
Gives the strength of five people!

445
00:41:45.613 --> 00:41:48.309
I think your cheese
done slid off your biscuit.


446
00:41:48.349 --> 00:41:51.648
You never see me chalk the line
for no white kid like you done.


447
00:41:51.685 --> 00:41:54.483
- You told me to!
- I didn't tell you to get us killed.


448
00:41:56.390 --> 00:42:00.656
This uniform don't change nothing for
us. This is a white man's war, Train.


449
00:42:00.694 --> 00:42:05.427
Negroes ain't got nothing to do with
this. This boy ain't got no life nohow.


450
00:42:05.466 --> 00:42:08.560
Why he don't? Hmm?

451
00:42:08.602 --> 00:42:12.663
A life of goodness is not what these
white folk has chosen for they children.


452
00:42:12.706 --> 00:42:14.936
Look at me.

453
00:42:16.744 --> 00:42:20.874
Good book says it, 
Proverbs 22:16.

454
00:42:20.915 --> 00:42:25.943
"Raise up a child the way you want him
to go, and he will not depart from it."


455
00:42:25.986 --> 00:42:27.954
Now, he's trained to hate.

456
00:42:29.890 --> 00:42:33.189
Shit, his life ain't worth
a dollar of Chinese money.


457
00:42:33.227 --> 00:42:35.923
Listen here, Bishop.

458
00:42:35.963 --> 00:42:39.160
This boy ain't done nothing to you.

459
00:42:39.200 --> 00:42:40.997
Mm-hm.

460
00:42:41.035 --> 00:42:43.731
You didn't want him before, did you?

461
00:42:48.876 --> 00:42:52.437
- Where you goin', Sam Train?
- Hey, Stamps, we movin' or not?


462
00:42:57.151 --> 00:43:00.314
We hold here till night.
Me and Bishop'll take first watch.


463
00:43:00.354 --> 00:43:04.188
Hector, you and Train take second.
Give the boy whatever first aid you got.


464
00:43:13.868 --> 00:43:17.463
What'd you get us into now, Diesel?

465
00:43:17.505 --> 00:43:22.169
It's always something with you,
big fella. Here, you gonna need these.


466
00:43:22.209 --> 00:43:24.643
Come on, kid.
[speaks Italian] Eat.


467
00:43:24.678 --> 00:43:26.077
Eat.

468
00:43:27.081 --> 00:43:29.072
Come on.

469
00:43:29.116 --> 00:43:30.913
He won't take the medicine.

470
00:43:37.658 --> 00:43:39.717
Go on, give it here.

471
00:43:39.760 --> 00:43:42.126
You want some chocolate, boy?

472
00:43:45.232 --> 00:43:48.167
I wouldn't get attached.
He'll be dead in a week.


473
00:43:48.202 --> 00:43:53.162
I ain't never been this close
to a white person before, Hec.


474
00:43:53.207 --> 00:43:56.438
Never even touched one.
Not even a dead one.


475
00:43:56.477 --> 00:43:59.844
If this one dies, I'll give you
a whistle as a consolation prize.


476
00:43:59.880 --> 00:44:02.872
- You really think he'll die?
- Why worry about it?


477
00:44:02.917 --> 00:44:04.908
We could all be dead
in an hour anyway.


478
00:44:11.859 --> 00:44:13.884
Why you always kissing that thing, Hec?

479
00:44:13.928 --> 00:44:18.763
- Reminds me who my father is.
- I don't need help remembering my pa.


480
00:44:18.799 --> 00:44:22.428
His name's Chester.
Chester Train.


481
00:44:22.469 --> 00:44:24.300
Let's give this kid some water.

482
00:44:28.676 --> 00:44:29.700
[in Italian] Water.

483
00:44:33.847 --> 00:44:34.905
Arturo?

484
00:44:35.849 --> 00:44:38.181
Can I ask you something?

485
00:44:38.218 --> 00:44:39.617
What you want, boy?

486
00:44:39.653 --> 00:44:41.553
[in Italian] Can you
tell me who I am?

487
00:44:42.756 --> 00:44:45.691
Hector, you speak that Italian?
What's he saying?


488
00:44:45.726 --> 00:44:48.194
He said, "Who am I?"
But who's he talking to?


489
00:44:48.228 --> 00:44:50.253
Lord, I knew it!

490
00:44:50.297 --> 00:44:52.993
I could see it in his face!
Look at him, Hec.


491
00:44:53.033 --> 00:44:54.830
Shh! Quiet down.

492
00:44:54.868 --> 00:44:57.336
Good God!

493
00:44:57.371 --> 00:44:59.271
- He got the power!
- What power?


494
00:44:59.306 --> 00:45:03.333
God knows it. In the olden days,
everything could speak.


495
00:45:03.377 --> 00:45:05.777
- The trees, the birds.
- Shh!


496
00:45:05.813 --> 00:45:10.011
If you could hear them things,
then that mean you had it.


497
00:45:13.554 --> 00:45:18.218
This boy's standing
in the shadow of God, Hector.


498
00:45:18.258 --> 00:45:22.388
Thank you, Jesus! Thank you for standing
on Your holy righteous word, Lord!


499
00:45:22.429 --> 00:45:25.193
Hallelujah! Thank you, Jesus!

500
00:45:45.319 --> 00:45:46.877
As you were.

501
00:46:14.281 --> 00:46:17.910
- General Almond.
- Colonel.


502
00:46:17.951 --> 00:46:20.784
I have a photo you should see, sir.

503
00:46:20.821 --> 00:46:24.917
Forget that a minute. How bad
are the numbers from yesterday?


504
00:46:24.958 --> 00:46:27.552
- Bad, sir.
- And lke gets mad when he gives me


505
00:46:27.594 --> 00:46:30.427
waiters and shoeshine boys
to fight the Krauts with.


506
00:46:30.464 --> 00:46:33.490
Germans are dug in.
And that gun at La Spezia's killing us.


507
00:46:33.534 --> 00:46:37.994
Fifteen thousand colored soldiers.
One in four is a casualty.


508
00:46:38.038 --> 00:46:41.132
And all I'm hearing about
is one goddamned gun?


509
00:46:41.175 --> 00:46:45.077
We have guns, too, here.
Look, see, colonel? I got one.


510
00:46:45.112 --> 00:46:49.742
This colored division...
This is an experiment, Jack.


511
00:46:49.783 --> 00:46:54.846
An experiment. These are the first lady
Eleanor Roosevelt's niggers. Not ours.


512
00:46:54.888 --> 00:46:59.757
- Sir, I respectfully disagree.
- That's why they sent you here, Jack.


513
00:46:59.793 --> 00:47:02.557
To lead me into the New World.

514
00:47:04.264 --> 00:47:08.030
A gift from the Brits.
Taken at 11,000 feet. See?


515
00:47:08.068 --> 00:47:11.560
That's a German buildup at
Lama Di Sotto. Two or three regiments.


516
00:47:11.605 --> 00:47:14.540
- Surprise attack you worried about?
- I hope not.


517
00:47:14.575 --> 00:47:16.372
I got corroboration from a partisan.

518
00:47:16.410 --> 00:47:18.901
Anybody crush grapes
with feet can't be trusted.


519
00:47:18.946 --> 00:47:20.846
Get some Krauts to confirm.

520
00:47:20.881 --> 00:47:23.645
Already working on it, sir.
Captain Rudden!


521
00:47:26.987 --> 00:47:30.582
- Good evening, general.
- Come.


522
00:47:30.624 --> 00:47:34.321
Germans may be planning counter-
offensive down the Serchio Valley.


523
00:47:34.361 --> 00:47:37.353
We need a POW to confirm.
You running patrols there?


524
00:47:37.397 --> 00:47:40.230
George Company has a squad
sitting right in that area.


525
00:47:40.267 --> 00:47:42.531
- How?
- They pushed across the Serchio


526
00:47:42.569 --> 00:47:46.266
beyond Hill Maine at the weak point.
I heard them call for artillery.


527
00:47:46.306 --> 00:47:50.504
Might've broken Jerry's hold
on the river. Captain Nokes didn't fire.


528
00:47:50.544 --> 00:47:53.308
- Why not?
- He couldn't see 'em, sir.


529
00:47:53.347 --> 00:47:55.781
Didn't believe they crossed,
they got hung up.


530
00:47:55.816 --> 00:47:59.252
I had Fox Company positioned
down the river from George Company.


531
00:47:59.286 --> 00:48:02.255
Got pretty hot over there.
Four of 'em right up a mountain.


532
00:48:02.289 --> 00:48:04.519
Got weapons and a radio
if they're alive.


533
00:48:04.558 --> 00:48:07.288
- Who are the four men?
- Shouldn't be hard to find out.


534
00:48:07.327 --> 00:48:09.795
One of them's the biggest Negro
you've ever seen in your life.


535
00:48:09.830 --> 00:48:11.855
Mmm.

536
00:48:11.899 --> 00:48:14.993
Very well then. Dismissed.

537
00:48:21.942 --> 00:48:24.410
[door shuts]

538
00:49:19.867 --> 00:49:22.199
[speaking German]
My God, I've had it.


539
00:49:22.236 --> 00:49:23.760
Come on, it's enough.

540
00:49:24.905 --> 00:49:25.929
Yeah, let's go.

541
00:49:27.741 --> 00:49:29.208
I need something to eat.

542
00:49:30.544 --> 00:49:34.605
[speaking Italian]
The Germans are leaving!


543
00:49:35.749 --> 00:49:38.547
[bell tolling]

544
00:49:44.358 --> 00:49:48.021
[speaking German] Push it up
or I'll kill it right now.


545
00:49:48.061 --> 00:49:49.892
I'm pushing as hard
as I can.


546
00:49:49.930 --> 00:49:51.659
Pull, pull, pull.

547
00:49:51.698 --> 00:49:54.599
My goodness I'm hungry.

548
00:49:54.635 --> 00:49:58.901
Finally something to chew on,
rather than the slime they feed us.


549
00:50:02.843 --> 00:50:05.141
[in Italian] Goodbye meat.
Now there'll be nothing left.


550
00:50:05.178 --> 00:50:07.544
They won't get fat on it.

551
00:50:07.581 --> 00:50:09.139
Let's hope they choke on it.

552
00:50:09.182 --> 00:50:11.742
Shut up, the two of you!

553
00:50:11.785 --> 00:50:15.050
Now, let's see if your husband
will come back from Russia.


554
00:50:22.763 --> 00:50:24.230
Mary, Joseph, Jesus,

555
00:50:24.264 --> 00:50:27.028
tell us if we'll see him
or never see him again.


556
00:50:27.067 --> 00:50:28.557
Is he still alive?

557
00:50:28.602 --> 00:50:30.570
My eyes aren't
what they used to be.


558
00:50:30.604 --> 00:50:32.902
- [rattling table]
- Come on!


559
00:50:32.940 --> 00:50:34.237
So, so, so?

560
00:50:34.274 --> 00:50:37.607
We can't even joke? Come on.

561
00:50:39.012 --> 00:50:41.037
That thing is just a stupid kid's game.

562
00:50:41.081 --> 00:50:43.106
You're the usual scoundrel!

563
00:50:43.150 --> 00:50:45.550
Just because he carries
the Fascist Party card,


564
00:50:45.585 --> 00:50:46.609
he thinks he can do what he wants.

565
00:50:46.653 --> 00:50:48.120
Oh yes?

566
00:50:48.155 --> 00:50:51.522
Then who was it who took butter
from the Germans the other day?


567
00:50:51.558 --> 00:50:52.650
The Pope?

568
00:50:52.693 --> 00:50:54.752
Maybe, because it wasn't us.

569
00:50:54.795 --> 00:50:56.092
And the light?

570
00:50:56.129 --> 00:50:57.687
How did your electricity come back on?

571
00:50:57.731 --> 00:50:58.891
Papa.

572
00:50:58.932 --> 00:51:00.092
Come with me.

573
00:51:00.133 --> 00:51:01.157
Come with me.

574
00:51:02.135 --> 00:51:03.693
How did the light come back on?

575
00:51:03.737 --> 00:51:06.570
The truth will never
come out of his mouth.


576
00:51:16.049 --> 00:51:18.210
You would think that
after all these years,


577
00:51:18.251 --> 00:51:20.879
you would treat your friends better.

578
00:51:20.921 --> 00:51:23.287
What is wrong with you, Papa?

579
00:51:23.323 --> 00:51:24.415
Would you tell me?

580
00:51:28.862 --> 00:51:30.591
It's Natalina.

581
00:51:30.630 --> 00:51:32.063
What did she do?

582
00:51:32.099 --> 00:51:33.964
She put the evil
eye on me, that Witch.

583
00:51:34.001 --> 00:51:36.333
You still going on about the same story?

584
00:51:36.370 --> 00:51:39.601
The Germans stole your rabbits, not her.

585
00:51:41.141 --> 00:51:44.008
There's strange things going on.

586
00:51:44.044 --> 00:51:46.512
My electricity returned...

587
00:51:46.546 --> 00:51:48.446
from God knows where
after two and a half years.


588
00:51:48.482 --> 00:51:50.143
I was going to ask you about that.

589
00:51:50.183 --> 00:51:53.880
Now I'm lit up like a carnival...

590
00:51:53.920 --> 00:51:57.651
for every bandit and German to see.

591
00:51:57.691 --> 00:52:01.354
It's Natalina's fault. She wants to see
me dead and buried behind the Church.


592
00:52:01.395 --> 00:52:02.794
What are you talking about?

593
00:52:04.564 --> 00:52:06.361
She prays for you every day.

594
00:52:08.535 --> 00:52:09.763
Know what I say?

595
00:52:10.971 --> 00:52:16.068
You go back in there
and apologize to your friends.


596
00:52:16.109 --> 00:52:18.441
Tell everyone that
Mussolini disgusts you,


597
00:52:18.478 --> 00:52:21.208
and that you are not a Fascist anymore.

598
00:52:21.248 --> 00:52:25.412
Il Duce made us a world power again.

599
00:52:25.452 --> 00:52:28.285
His only mistake was to get in bed
with that imbecile Hitler.


600
00:52:28.321 --> 00:52:30.881
Papa, II Duce betrayed Italy.

601
00:52:30.924 --> 00:52:33.688
And now you'll see
how this is going to end.


602
00:52:33.727 --> 00:52:36.025
You are still so young, my child.

603
00:52:36.063 --> 00:52:37.963
You don't know the ways of the world.

604
00:52:37.998 --> 00:52:40.489
But you will learn.

605
00:52:40.534 --> 00:52:42.627
And from whom?

606
00:52:42.669 --> 00:52:44.000
From a Fascist like you?

607
00:52:45.005 --> 00:52:47.132
You're just like your mother.

608
00:52:47.174 --> 00:52:48.903
And she used to tell you
that Blackshirts


609
00:52:48.942 --> 00:52:50.842
are only good for hiding dirt.

610
00:52:50.877 --> 00:52:52.037
Okay, let's go.

611
00:52:56.083 --> 00:52:57.778
[knocking on door]

612
00:52:59.219 --> 00:53:00.584
Germans!!!

613
00:53:02.289 --> 00:53:03.381
It's your house.

614
00:53:14.267 --> 00:53:15.393
Holy Mother of God.

615
00:53:23.143 --> 00:53:24.474
It's okay.

616
00:53:24.511 --> 00:53:26.479
It's okay.

617
00:53:26.513 --> 00:53:27.605
It's okay, it's okay.

618
00:53:30.884 --> 00:53:33.512
Hector, ask who's in charge.
Tell them we're Americans.


619
00:53:37.624 --> 00:53:39.114
[in Italian] Americans?

620
00:53:39.159 --> 00:53:41.184
[in English] Me, too. Half.

621
00:53:41.228 --> 00:53:42.490
[in Italian] Half.

622
00:53:42.529 --> 00:53:45.123
[in English] Me sister Ida, half.

623
00:53:45.165 --> 00:53:47.929
[in Italian] We called her little Ida,
because she was the baby.


624
00:53:47.968 --> 00:53:50.232
Put us together,
we make one American.


625
00:53:50.270 --> 00:53:51.703
[in Italian] Okay, wait. Wait.

626
00:53:51.738 --> 00:53:54.605
Wait. Wait. Wait.

627
00:53:54.641 --> 00:53:55.869
Thank you.

628
00:53:55.909 --> 00:53:57.171
Who's in charge here?

629
00:54:09.055 --> 00:54:11.523
Anybody here speak English?

630
00:54:14.060 --> 00:54:15.322
[in Italian]
Where are the Germans?


631
00:54:15.362 --> 00:54:18.593
Everywhere. Boom, boom.

632
00:54:18.632 --> 00:54:21.362
My name is Renata.

633
00:54:23.270 --> 00:54:28.173
- Where'd you learn English?
- I was nanny for a British family.


634
00:54:28.208 --> 00:54:32.770
And a jolly good tuck-in-the-bed
tinkerer you must be.


635
00:54:32.812 --> 00:54:36.748
- You can nanny me. Want a Camel?
- Cool it, Bishop.


636
00:54:36.783 --> 00:54:40.947
I'm Staff Sergeant Aubrey Stamps.
We got a boy that needs help.


637
00:54:40.987 --> 00:54:42.716
[in Italian]
A boy? He has a boy.


638
00:54:44.925 --> 00:54:46.415
Oh, my God.

639
00:54:47.394 --> 00:54:49.487
Is he alive? Put him here.

640
00:54:49.529 --> 00:54:51.121
Slow. Slowly.

641
00:54:53.233 --> 00:54:54.962
Where did you find him?

642
00:54:55.001 --> 00:54:57.196
[Hector] On the Mountain.
Do you know him?


643
00:54:57.237 --> 00:54:59.296
[Natalina]
No, I don't know him.


644
00:54:59.339 --> 00:55:01.807
But he can stay here
until he gets better.


645
00:55:01.841 --> 00:55:05.038
Tell them we're taking the boy
to a hospital. They can come.


646
00:55:05.078 --> 00:55:08.309
They need to evacuate.
We'll escort them down the mountain.


647
00:55:08.348 --> 00:55:11.112
[in Italian] We're going to a hospital.
You can come with us.


648
00:55:11.985 --> 00:55:14.044
The hospital around the corner?

649
00:55:14.087 --> 00:55:16.282
The Germans are everywhere.

650
00:55:16.323 --> 00:55:18.348
Torrite, Rontano, Mezzana.

651
00:55:18.391 --> 00:55:20.859
All the way to Barga
and down to the Serchio.


652
00:55:20.894 --> 00:55:23.692
I don't know how you
got past Vergemoli.


653
00:55:23.730 --> 00:55:27.393
The only way to Pietrasanta...

654
00:55:27.434 --> 00:55:29.095
where the Americans might be...

655
00:55:29.135 --> 00:55:30.659
is over that way,

656
00:55:31.671 --> 00:55:33.696
over the Mountain of the Sleeping Man.

657
00:55:34.941 --> 00:55:36.169
Says we're surrounded.

658
00:55:36.209 --> 00:55:38.370
Doesn't know how we got
past German lines,


659
00:55:38.411 --> 00:55:41.642
but the only way we might find
some Americans is up there.


660
00:55:41.681 --> 00:55:44.047
- The Mountain of the Sleeping Man.
- Sleeping Man?


661
00:55:44.084 --> 00:55:47.485
- [in Italian] What is that?
- It's a legend.


662
00:55:47.520 --> 00:55:53.481
A shepherd fell in love with a girl
who would not love him back.


663
00:55:53.526 --> 00:55:56.222
So he lays across the Mountain...

664
00:55:56.263 --> 00:55:58.663
to protect her from the wind and rain.

665
00:55:58.698 --> 00:56:02.896
He still lies there today,
to protect us all.


666
00:56:02.936 --> 00:56:07.305
Legend has it that
one day he will awaken.


667
00:56:10.076 --> 00:56:12.636
A legend about a shepherd
that fell in love...


668
00:56:12.679 --> 00:56:14.977
Whatever she's saying,
we gotta rest until sunup.


669
00:56:15.015 --> 00:56:17.279
- OK.
- Stay here? No, no.


670
00:56:17.317 --> 00:56:19.046
<i>Stay here. Si, si.</i>

671
00:56:19.085 --> 00:56:22.077
If they sing to the Krauts,
we will pull a trigger on this


672
00:56:22.122 --> 00:56:25.956
and tell the hammer to hurry. Won't be
nothing but powder and steel here.


673
00:56:25.992 --> 00:56:29.553
We are not Germans.
We are Italians.


674
00:56:29.596 --> 00:56:31.962
- Full blood.
- And what are we? Half blood?


675
00:56:34.567 --> 00:56:36.865
[in Italian]
We should take him...


676
00:56:36.903 --> 00:56:38.632
and put him to bed.

677
00:56:38.672 --> 00:56:41.903
The boy stays here. He's sick.

678
00:56:58.992 --> 00:57:00.459
<i>Heil Hitler!</i>

679
00:57:29.989 --> 00:57:32.719
[in German]
Catching up on your reading?


680
00:57:32.759 --> 00:57:35.887
Yes, Colonel, I'm informing myself
about the enemy.


681
00:57:35.929 --> 00:57:40.263
The Partisans often take their names
from banned poetry and literature.


682
00:57:40.300 --> 00:57:42.268
This helps us identify them.

683
00:57:42.302 --> 00:57:44.497
Who is the poet?

684
00:57:44.537 --> 00:57:46.266
Giovanni Pascoli.

685
00:57:46.306 --> 00:57:51.767
Do you think it's appropriate
to waste your time reading poetry?


686
00:57:51.811 --> 00:57:57.681
In the past nine months we've seen
a sharp rise in Partisan activity.


687
00:57:57.717 --> 00:58:00.015
What are you planning to do about it?

688
00:58:00.053 --> 00:58:04.114
Colonel, we are down
to shovels and mule shit.


689
00:58:04.157 --> 00:58:05.624
My men are exhausted.

690
00:58:05.658 --> 00:58:07.853
We need ammo and food.

691
00:58:07.894 --> 00:58:10.522
Food? You want food?

692
00:58:10.563 --> 00:58:13.259
You can suck icicles
in Russia...


693
00:58:13.299 --> 00:58:18.635
like you did before your so-called
neck wound brought you back here.


694
00:58:18.671 --> 00:58:22.232
You think you're the first
to command hungry troops?


695
00:58:22.275 --> 00:58:25.438
I mean no disrespect, Colonel.

696
00:58:27.113 --> 00:58:30.412
Good. Listen closely.

697
00:58:30.450 --> 00:58:33.317
I have come too far to repeat myself.

698
00:58:33.353 --> 00:58:37.619
First, there is a peasant, a terrorist.

699
00:58:37.657 --> 00:58:42.390
Named The Great Butterfly.
He's causing many problems.


700
00:58:42.429 --> 00:58:45.057
He's hiding in these mountains.
Find him.


701
00:58:45.098 --> 00:58:48.363
When he is found,
issue Directive Bandenbefehl...


702
00:58:48.401 --> 00:58:51.063
to him and his criminal friends.

703
00:58:51.104 --> 00:58:52.162
Bandenbefehl?

704
00:58:52.205 --> 00:58:54.833
Is there an echo out here?

705
00:58:54.874 --> 00:58:59.004
General Kesselring's standing
field order for the Italian Republic.


706
00:58:59.045 --> 00:59:01.536
At a commander's sole discretion,

707
00:59:01.581 --> 00:59:04.379
for every one German soldier killed,

708
00:59:04.417 --> 00:59:06.783
we execute ten Italian civilians.

709
00:59:06.820 --> 00:59:12.349
You should have been capable to execute
that order at least once in nine months.


710
00:59:12.392 --> 00:59:16.021
Colonel, with all due respect,
if I execute this order...


711
00:59:16.062 --> 00:59:18.587
my men would kill innocent civilians.

712
00:59:18.631 --> 00:59:22.260
It would be a violation
of the Geneva Convention.


713
00:59:22.302 --> 00:59:27.069
Partisans are not civilians;
they are terrorists.


714
00:59:27.106 --> 00:59:30.041
They are not protected
under the Geneva Convention.


715
00:59:30.076 --> 00:59:32.442
Bandenbefehl!

716
00:59:32.479 --> 00:59:33.639
Bandenbefehl.

717
00:59:35.982 --> 00:59:39.349
Secondly, the surprise
counterattack is still planned.


718
00:59:39.385 --> 00:59:43.879
I will tighten supply lines
with food and ammunition.


719
00:59:43.923 --> 00:59:46.221
And three:

720
00:59:46.259 --> 00:59:50.127
A delicate intelligence matter
of the utmost priority.


721
00:59:56.069 --> 00:59:58.936
We are missing a Corporal...

722
00:59:58.972 --> 01:00:02.601
from the 35th Regiment,

723
01:00:02.642 --> 01:00:06.635
Name: Hans Brandt,
gone AWOL three weeks ago.


724
01:00:06.679 --> 01:00:09.648
[Eichholz] We have some every day.
What's so special about him?


725
01:00:10.583 --> 01:00:13.051
You and I are not here...

726
01:00:13.086 --> 01:00:16.920
to question the Führer's orders.

727
01:00:16.956 --> 01:00:19.516
You are to send out a search party.

728
01:00:19.559 --> 01:00:21.049
Find him.

729
01:00:21.094 --> 01:00:22.789
Don't let him escape.

730
01:00:22.829 --> 01:00:24.820
And when you have him...

731
01:00:25.865 --> 01:00:28.732
get word to me immediately.

732
01:00:37.877 --> 01:00:39.606
Let's go!

733
01:00:50.590 --> 01:00:54.185
<i>[in Italian] If I am no longer
that lamp...</i>


734
01:00:54.227 --> 01:00:57.025
<i>which flickers in front
of a sweet Maria.</i>


735
01:00:57.063 --> 01:00:58.530
[in German] What does that mean?

736
01:00:59.766 --> 01:01:01.563
God help this poor bastard Brandt.

737
01:01:02.435 --> 01:01:03.834
Whatever he's done,

738
01:01:03.870 --> 01:01:06.737
it's no worse than what anyone else
has done in this war.


739
01:01:07.473 --> 01:01:08.838
Mount a search party.

740
01:01:08.875 --> 01:01:10.866
We have to find him first,

741
01:01:10.910 --> 01:01:13.902
hold him and give him a few days...

742
01:01:13.947 --> 01:01:17.041
before Pflueger pulls out
his teeth, one by one.


743
01:01:17.083 --> 01:01:18.107
Yes.

744
01:01:18.551 --> 01:01:20.917
I'll be relieved when this war is over.

745
01:01:20.954 --> 01:01:22.819
I want to return to my family.

746
01:01:51.851 --> 01:01:54.046
[in Italian]
I've watched you grow up.


747
01:01:54.087 --> 01:01:56.351
But you haven't become much.

748
01:01:56.389 --> 01:01:57.856
And he can't do much.

749
01:01:57.890 --> 01:01:59.755
- You're laughing at me?
- Of course.


750
01:01:59.792 --> 01:02:02.260
Where did you get that?

751
01:02:02.295 --> 01:02:03.785
So many things you want to know.

752
01:02:03.830 --> 01:02:04.922
Here. Take it and eat.

753
01:02:04.964 --> 01:02:06.295
Give me some, too.

754
01:02:06.332 --> 01:02:08.596
Are you afraid you're
not going to get any?


755
01:02:08.635 --> 01:02:09.795
Here. Grow.

756
01:02:09.836 --> 01:02:11.463
Give me a chestnut, too.

757
01:02:13.139 --> 01:02:14.936
My goodness, you stink like a sheep.

758
01:02:14.974 --> 01:02:16.635
Hey, leave me alone.

759
01:02:16.676 --> 01:02:18.610
Aren't you the dandy?

760
01:02:18.645 --> 01:02:20.408
Ah, he's offended.

761
01:02:25.785 --> 01:02:28.413
What the fuck are you doing, Peppi?

762
01:02:28.454 --> 01:02:30.149
You have to be on the lookout.

763
01:02:30.189 --> 01:02:33.420
If I had been a German,
you would all be dead... 1, 2, 3.


764
01:02:33.459 --> 01:02:35.086
I almost choked.

765
01:02:36.129 --> 01:02:37.756
You wait here.

766
01:02:52.979 --> 01:02:54.241
My friend.

767
01:02:54.280 --> 01:02:56.544
The Americans are getting closer.

768
01:02:57.817 --> 01:02:59.808
We have to warn them about
the Germans' counterattack.


769
01:02:59.852 --> 01:03:01.979
They know it already, for sure.

770
01:03:03.056 --> 01:03:05.081
You? How are you?

771
01:03:05.124 --> 01:03:07.354
Me? I'm okay.

772
01:03:07.393 --> 01:03:08.451
You?

773
01:03:08.494 --> 01:03:10.985
I always have Marco's
face in front of my eyes.


774
01:03:14.333 --> 01:03:15.561
Don't worry about that.

775
01:03:15.601 --> 01:03:20.834
My brother is dead.
Nobody cares about him any more.


776
01:03:20.873 --> 01:03:21.999
I care.

777
01:03:22.041 --> 01:03:23.440
In your opinion...

778
01:03:24.343 --> 01:03:25.742
when we will be in front of God,

779
01:03:25.778 --> 01:03:28.611
if we ever get there,

780
01:03:28.648 --> 01:03:31.617
is he going to ask us
for our political card?


781
01:03:31.651 --> 01:03:34.620
Is he going to say,
"Marco, no... Ludovico, no.


782
01:03:34.654 --> 01:03:38.146
You're not allowed in
because you're Fascists."


783
01:03:38.191 --> 01:03:42.787
What's the difference between
us and them in the eyes of God?


784
01:03:42.829 --> 01:03:45.093
You're asking yourself
too many questions.


785
01:03:45.131 --> 01:03:48.726
If you think too much,
it will drive you crazy.


786
01:03:48.768 --> 01:03:51.362
And then who will kill the Germans?

787
01:03:51.404 --> 01:03:52.428
Hey.

788
01:03:54.674 --> 01:03:57.074
Anyway, what's done is done.

789
01:04:04.917 --> 01:04:09.217
George Company to 370,
George Company to 3-7, over.


790
01:04:13.559 --> 01:04:16.153
George Company to 370, over.

791
01:04:39.952 --> 01:04:42.648
[in Italian] Someone tell that
big beast to get out of my room.


792
01:04:42.688 --> 01:04:45.748
Shh! The Boy has a fever.

793
01:04:45.792 --> 01:04:48.420
He needs to eat and get some rest.

794
01:04:48.461 --> 01:04:50.452
Try thinking of others
every once in awhile.


795
01:05:00.373 --> 01:05:01.670
Arturo.

796
01:05:02.742 --> 01:05:05.210
The Chocolate Giant's Castle...

797
01:05:05.244 --> 01:05:07.075
if you could only see it.

798
01:05:07.113 --> 01:05:09.604
It's enormous.

799
01:05:09.649 --> 01:05:11.810
No, even bigger.

800
01:05:12.652 --> 01:05:15.212
Of course I saw it.

801
01:05:15.254 --> 01:05:17.381
It's all made of chocolate.

802
01:05:17.423 --> 01:05:19.391
You break a piece off,

803
01:05:19.425 --> 01:05:21.222
and it grows back.

804
01:05:23.362 --> 01:05:25.626
Yes, I did save a piece for you.

805
01:05:33.105 --> 01:05:34.595
Good heavens.

806
01:05:34.640 --> 01:05:36.130
Something's not right.

807
01:05:36.175 --> 01:05:37.574
Someone put the evil eye on him.

808
01:05:37.610 --> 01:05:39.908
Bewitched or not, he's got to go.

809
01:05:39.946 --> 01:05:42.779
- To where?
- With the Americans.


810
01:05:42.815 --> 01:05:44.476
I think he brings good luck.
The Boy stays.


811
01:05:44.517 --> 01:05:46.144
This is my house.

812
01:05:46.185 --> 01:05:47.550
I have a house too.

813
01:05:48.521 --> 01:05:49.920
Natalina.

814
01:05:49.956 --> 01:05:51.446
What do you think?

815
01:05:51.490 --> 01:05:54.550
I say this Boy
is talking to the Devil.

816
01:05:54.594 --> 01:05:56.118
We need a Priest here.

817
01:05:56.162 --> 01:05:58.323
He doesn't need a Priest.
He needs a Doctor.


818
01:05:58.364 --> 01:06:01.231
A Priest can take
the Devil out of him.


819
01:06:01.267 --> 01:06:04.293
Train, get up. 
We gotta book.

820
01:06:08.808 --> 01:06:10.002
[Train] Excuse me.

821
01:06:10.042 --> 01:06:13.478
Hey, boy. Hey.

822
01:06:13.512 --> 01:06:17.573
Time for you
to take your medicine again.


823
01:06:18.384 --> 01:06:19.942
Here it comes. Ready?

824
01:06:19.986 --> 01:06:22.648
[humming]

825
01:06:23.689 --> 01:06:26.180
There. Thank you.

826
01:06:27.860 --> 01:06:29.919
Get you some of that soup, boy.

827
01:06:30.997 --> 01:06:32.089
Mmm.

828
01:06:36.736 --> 01:06:39.534
- Yes.
- He would not eat before.


829
01:06:42.675 --> 01:06:44.233
Here you go, boy.

830
01:06:46.112 --> 01:06:48.046
It's all over your shirt.

831
01:06:50.783 --> 01:06:54.344
- Come on, boy. Let's go.
- [in Italian] My Chocolate Giant.


832
01:06:54.387 --> 01:06:58.255
- OK, sarge. We ready.
- Oh, hold on, hold on, hold on.


833
01:06:58.291 --> 01:07:01.192
We? Boy, where the hell "we" goin'?

834
01:07:01.227 --> 01:07:03.320
You wasn't chiseling him,
we wouldn't be here.


835
01:07:03.362 --> 01:07:05.990
- You think Nokes is lookin' for us?
- What?


836
01:07:07.566 --> 01:07:10.330
Hector been tryin' to fix that radio
since we got here.


837
01:07:10.369 --> 01:07:12.132
- Shh!
- What?


838
01:07:15.975 --> 01:07:17.567
<i>Arrive- damn-derci.</i>

839
01:07:22.915 --> 01:07:28.285
Hector. We gotta bail. Ask the old man
if he'll show us another way outta here.


840
01:07:28.321 --> 01:07:31.722
- Maybe we can reach the 366.
- We can't get five feet outta here


841
01:07:31.757 --> 01:07:34.555
<i>without being flavor of the week
for the Guten Tags.</i>


842
01:07:34.593 --> 01:07:38.552
<i>These people survived for years
without mortars. Stay with the paisans.</i>


843
01:07:38.597 --> 01:07:41.896
You wanna stay here and play house,
go ahead, but I'm bookin'.


844
01:07:41.934 --> 01:07:45.529
Ask the old man if he'll show us
another way outta these mountains.


845
01:07:45.571 --> 01:07:50.201
Tell him we'll pay him. We got plenty of
that funny money they use around here.


846
01:07:50.242 --> 01:07:52.403
[speaks Italian]
Can you show us a safe path?


847
01:07:52.445 --> 01:07:54.310
There is no safe way.

848
01:07:54.347 --> 01:07:55.974
Germans. Boom! Boom!

849
01:07:56.174 --> 01:07:57.732
You know a way.

850
01:07:57.775 --> 01:08:00.972
Franco was the mailman,
ask him. I'm too old.


851
01:08:01.012 --> 01:08:04.379
Me? I have to deliver the mail.

852
01:08:04.415 --> 01:08:06.474
What mail, you old crazy fool?

853
01:08:06.518 --> 01:08:10.181
Old crazy fool? You're the old crazy,
like your mother and your father.


854
01:08:10.221 --> 01:08:12.451
- I know.
- You know?


855
01:08:12.490 --> 01:08:15.823
I know a way. I take you.

856
01:08:15.860 --> 01:08:17.327
[in Italian] What did you say?

857
01:08:19.597 --> 01:08:21.929
What did my daughter say?

858
01:08:21.966 --> 01:08:24.764
[in Italian] I have
nothing to do with this.


859
01:08:24.802 --> 01:08:27.498
Bishop. What you think?

860
01:08:27.539 --> 01:08:31.339
Little Red Riding Hood
lead us through the woods?


861
01:08:31.376 --> 01:08:33.844
I don't know, sarge.

862
01:08:33.878 --> 01:08:38.178
I mean, she fine. 
Man, she fine.

863
01:08:38.216 --> 01:08:42.243
I hear that they got
lady Mussolinis, too.


864
01:08:42.287 --> 01:08:44.255
Could be a trap.

865
01:08:46.858 --> 01:08:48.849
Hector.

866
01:08:48.893 --> 01:08:51.293
You the boss, staff sergeant.

867
01:08:51.329 --> 01:08:54.093
No good. No. No good.

868
01:08:55.533 --> 01:08:58.900
All of a sudden the old man
speaks some English, huh?


869
01:09:02.006 --> 01:09:03.496
[in Italian] Are you crazy in the head?

870
01:09:03.541 --> 01:09:04.940
Keep out of this.

871
01:09:05.810 --> 01:09:07.334
I forbid you to go.

872
01:09:07.378 --> 01:09:10.472
I don't need your permission.
Understand?


873
01:09:10.515 --> 01:09:12.710
You're still my daughter.

874
01:09:12.750 --> 01:09:16.709
Look, we'll find a way
outta here. Let's go.


875
01:09:28.666 --> 01:09:31.226
<i>Bye-bye, Americani.</i>

876
01:09:31.269 --> 01:09:33.237
Renata. Come away.

877
01:09:33.271 --> 01:09:34.465
No!

878
01:09:35.740 --> 01:09:37.970
Oh!

879
01:09:38.009 --> 01:09:41.911
Cigarette? Chocolate?

880
01:09:41.946 --> 01:09:43.675
[Stamps] Hell, no!

881
01:09:46.084 --> 01:09:47.608
[in Italian] Shove it up your ass.

882
01:09:49.721 --> 01:09:53.817
Sergeant Stamps out there
fussin' over what side to get back to.


883
01:09:53.858 --> 01:09:57.021
It don't mean nothin', boy.

884
01:09:57.061 --> 01:09:59.529
Me, I ain't got a side.

885
01:10:03.034 --> 01:10:06.731
[speaking Italian] Arturo said
that if you turn your head...


886
01:10:06.771 --> 01:10:08.363
it will be my birthday.

887
01:10:08.406 --> 01:10:12.467
I'll get toys and lots of candy.

888
01:10:12.510 --> 01:10:14.842
Now, please turn your head.

889
01:10:15.813 --> 01:10:17.804
Please turn your head.

890
01:10:19.417 --> 01:10:23.148
I can't understand your words, boy.

891
01:10:23.187 --> 01:10:25.087
But I don't need to.

892
01:10:25.123 --> 01:10:30.060
You see, everything you touch,
you brings good to it. You do.


893
01:10:31.462 --> 01:10:34.989
See this little thing here?
lt'll make you invisible.


894
01:10:35.033 --> 01:10:40.733
Give you the strength of five people.
You ain't got to own nothin'.


895
01:10:40.772 --> 01:10:43.400
Ain't got to be a big somebody.

896
01:10:43.441 --> 01:10:47.036
All you got to do
is believe in it, boy.

897
01:10:50.248 --> 01:10:52.239
Go on, boy. Go on.

898
01:10:57.255 --> 01:11:00.019
[in Italian] Can you turn
your head like this? See?


899
01:11:00.058 --> 01:11:03.755
God made this thing here
through man's hand.


900
01:11:03.795 --> 01:11:09.256
But the Lord gived it
shape and purpose.


901
01:11:09.300 --> 01:11:11.768
And through this little thing here,

902
01:11:11.803 --> 01:11:14.704
God gives you somethin' else, boy.

903
01:11:14.739 --> 01:11:18.505
You know what it is?
I'ma tell ya, I'ma tell ya.


904
01:11:18.543 --> 01:11:20.272
It's a secret.

905
01:11:21.379 --> 01:11:22.778
Miracles.

906
01:11:25.683 --> 01:11:27.514
[in Italian] Listen, 
Chocolate Giant.

907
01:11:27.552 --> 01:11:29.486
You've got to do what I say.

908
01:11:29.520 --> 01:11:32.318
Turn your head
so it will be my birthday.


909
01:11:32.357 --> 01:11:34.552
You want me
to stay eight forever?


910
01:11:36.094 --> 01:11:37.493
Turn your head.

911
01:11:38.696 --> 01:11:40.357
Arturo!

912
01:11:41.032 --> 01:11:43.364
Yes! I did it!

913
01:11:43.401 --> 01:11:44.891
I'm nine years old!

914
01:11:44.936 --> 01:11:47.700
Hey! Yes!

915
01:11:47.739 --> 01:11:49.434
Nine years old!

916
01:11:49.874 --> 01:11:51.466
Hurray!

917
01:11:51.509 --> 01:11:52.976
Nine years old!

918
01:11:53.010 --> 01:11:54.341
Boy, you got the spirit?

919
01:11:54.379 --> 01:11:56.973
[Arturo, in Italian]
I did it! Nine years old!


920
01:11:57.014 --> 01:12:00.472
You know up high, down low?
Gimme five.


921
01:12:00.518 --> 01:12:03.351
Gimme five. All right. All right.

922
01:12:03.388 --> 01:12:05.549
Up high.

923
01:12:07.291 --> 01:12:10.988
Up high, gimme five. OK.

924
01:12:11.028 --> 01:12:13.861
Gimme five. Gimme five.

925
01:12:13.898 --> 01:12:17.197
Up high. Down low.

926
01:12:17.235 --> 01:12:19.430
Down low. Too slow.

927
01:12:23.007 --> 01:12:25.271
You know that one? Gimme five.

928
01:12:25.309 --> 01:12:27.004
Up high.

929
01:12:27.044 --> 01:12:28.568
Down low.

930
01:12:28.613 --> 01:12:30.103
Too slow.

931
01:12:31.382 --> 01:12:33.646
Let's see if I got some chocolate here.

932
01:12:35.653 --> 01:12:37.348
You like chocolate?

933
01:12:37.388 --> 01:12:39.618
[giggles]

934
01:12:39.657 --> 01:12:42.148
Yeah.

935
01:12:42.193 --> 01:12:43.660
How'd I get up here?

936
01:12:43.694 --> 01:12:47.152
The only place where
the Germans would not be


937
01:12:47.198 --> 01:12:50.497
is through the mountain
in Pietrasanta, Lucca.


938
01:12:50.535 --> 01:12:53.504
It's here. See?

939
01:12:53.538 --> 01:12:57.941
And that's where I think you
gonna find your people.


940
01:12:57.975 --> 01:13:01.240
- Here you go, Hector.
- Thanks, Train.


941
01:13:09.187 --> 01:13:10.586
Boy!

942
01:13:14.892 --> 01:13:17.019
[speaking Italian]
How do you know?


943
01:13:17.061 --> 01:13:18.255
Is that true?

944
01:13:19.330 --> 01:13:21.355
Yeah, I know.

945
01:13:21.399 --> 01:13:22.730
[in Italian]
Who are you talking to?


946
01:13:22.767 --> 01:13:24.894
- To Arturo.
- Arturo?


947
01:13:24.936 --> 01:13:25.960
Who's Arturo?

948
01:13:26.003 --> 01:13:27.334
My friend.

949
01:13:29.340 --> 01:13:30.739
And where is he?

950
01:13:32.009 --> 01:13:34.034
Over there, do you see?

951
01:13:34.078 --> 01:13:36.137
He's shy in front of other people.

952
01:13:46.457 --> 01:13:47.651
Hey.

953
01:14:16.120 --> 01:14:17.781
Arturo, what do you think?

954
01:14:18.389 --> 01:14:19.617
Shall we help him?

955
01:14:21.158 --> 01:14:22.921
<i>[man on radio]
Three-seventy to Stamps.</i>


956
01:14:22.960 --> 01:14:24.587
[in Italian] We did it.

957
01:14:24.629 --> 01:14:27.120
<i>Three-seventy to Stamps.</i>

958
01:14:27.164 --> 01:14:30.133
Three-seventy to Stamps. Over.

959
01:14:34.105 --> 01:14:38.064
Three-seventy, this is Negron,
George Company, over.


960
01:14:38.109 --> 01:14:40.475
Got him, sir. I got the lost squad.

961
01:14:40.511 --> 01:14:42.206
Get up.

962
